{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/17652685", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/17652685/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/17652685/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/freebayes/freebayes/releases/tag/v1.3.0", "id": 17652685, "author": {"login": "ekg", "id": 145425, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTQyNQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/145425?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg", "html_url": "https://github.com/ekg", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTE3NjUyNjg1", "tag_name": "v1.3.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Skipping regions with high coverage", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2019-05-29T10:56:46Z", "published_at": "2019-05-29T11:10:21Z", "assets": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/assets/12940033", "id": 12940033, "node_id": "MDEyOlJlbGVhc2VBc3NldDEyOTQwMDMz", "name": "freebayes-v1.3.0-1", "label": null, "uploader": {"login": "ekg", "id": 145425, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTQyNQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/145425?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg", "html_url": "https://github.com/ekg", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "content_type": "application/octet-stream", "state": "uploaded", "size": 5846352, "download_count": 175, "created_at": "2019-05-30T08:32:15Z", "updated_at": "2019-05-30T08:32:17Z", "browser_download_url": "https://github.com/freebayes/freebayes/releases/download/v1.3.0/freebayes-v1.3.0-1"}], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/tarball/v1.3.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/zipball/v1.3.0", "body": "For a long time, one of the most difficult aspects of using freebayes is that doesn't have a method to skip regions of high coverage. The alignment processing model greatly expands the memory usage relative to depth, leading to problems in high coverage regions.\r\n\r\nIn cases where coverage varies dramatically across the reference, such as by many orders of magnitude, this led to a need to calculate a coverage map and use this to establish a set of targets. Another approach is to break up the genome into regions of a given number of reads, which tends to normalize runtime across parallel jobs. Both of these approaches are rather complicated for many users to implement, and lead to problems.\r\n\r\nThis problem is particularly pronounced in the context of assembly polishing, where freebayes is seeing a lot of use. To minimize difficulty for groups using it in this manner (like the VGP), I've implemented a filter that allows us to skip regions of high coverage, `--skip-coverage`.\r\n\r\nI have also renamed the previously used `--max-coverage` to `--limit-coverage` to minimize confusion about its function. It applies deterministic read downsampling to drop to the desired coverage. This reduces genotyping cost, but it doesn't help improve runtime in cases of extreme depth because we have to spend a lot of time and memory processing the input alignments. Both options can be applied together, as they are independent.\r\n\r\nThis release bundles up a number of other changes from the last year.\r\n\r\nAttached to this release is an experimental static binary that should work on modern Linux systems. Note that this includes a minor bugfix to correct parameter parsing against v1.3.0."}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/10457870", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/10457870/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/releases/10457870/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/freebayes/freebayes/releases/tag/v1.2.0", "id": 10457870, "author": {"login": "ekg", "id": 145425, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTQyNQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/145425?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg", "html_url": "https://github.com/ekg", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ekg/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTEwNDU3ODcw", "tag_name": "v1.2.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Sensitive default input filters", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2018-04-09T15:09:32Z", "published_at": "2018-04-09T15:13:35Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/tarball/v1.2.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/freebayes/freebayes/zipball/v1.2.0", "body": "This release marks the integration of settings that I've been using for much of my work with freebayes for several years as default parameters. It sets the `--min-alternate-fraction` parameter to 0.05, which tends to improve sensitivity in almost all contexts I've tested. In addition, it sets the `--min-repeat-entropy` parameter to 1, which will tend to produce marginally more haplotype based calls where repeats are flanked by low-entropy sequence that may not be an exact repeat. These changes cause freebayes to produce more sites than before, so users should be aware and filter as appropriate. The previous settings are accessible via `-F 0.2 --min-repeat-entropy 0`."}
